fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.mapping

Interface EMFtoGraphMapping

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMapping, NeoEMFMapping

    public interface EMFtoGraphMapping
    Defines the methods that should be implemented to use Mogwa√Ø-ATL with a specific EMF to Graph mapping.

    The methods defined in this interface are called within the generated script and are responsible of retrieving EMF-related information inside a graph database. They are inspired from the ones defined in the ATL API.

    Most of the method have two implementations: one that takes the current element in its parameters and returns the computed value from this element, and another that only takes additional parameters and compute the value for all the element in the current GremlinPipeline, returning a Pipe or a Pipeline (see Pipe website for further information). Note that these method are implemented as simple wrappers in AbstractMapping, which can be extended by concrete mapping subclasses.

    A custom EMFtoGraphMapping can be provided to the Mogwai-ATL engine using the following code: 

     
 EMFtoGraphMapping myHelper = new // an implementation of this interface
 
 MogwaiQuery query = MogwaiATLQueryBuilder.newBuilder()
 	.fromFile(new File("myScript.gremlin"))
 	.bind(TransformationHelper.BINDING_NAME, helper)
 	.build();
    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL

      • allOfType

        Iterable<Vertex> allOfType(String typeName)
        Returns an Iterable containing all the instances of the type typeName.

        Note: result only contains strict instances of the given type. To get all the instances of typeName and its subclasses see allOfKind(String) and allOfKindPipeline(String).

        Parameters:
        typeName - the name of the metaclass to get the instances of
        Returns:
        an Iterable containing all the instances of the type typeName

      • newInstance

        Object newInstance(String typeName,
                   String typePackageNsURI)
        Creates a new instance of the type typeName.

        typePackageNsURI can be provided for mappings that support metaclasses defined in multiple EPackages. Note that this information may be optional or mandatory, depending on the mapping used.

        Parameters:
        typeName - the name of the metaclass to create an instance of
        typePackageNsURI - the URI of the EPackage that defines the metaclass typeName
        Returns:
        an Object representing the created instance of typeName

      • isTypeOf

        boolean isTypeOf(Vertex from,
                 String type)
        Returns whether from is an instance of type.

        Note: this method only checks if from is a strict instance of the type. To check if from is an instance of type or any of its subclasses see isKindOf(Vertex, String) and isKindOf(String).

        Parameters:
        from - the Vertex to check the type of
        type - the type to check
        Returns:
        true if from is an instance of type, false otherwise
        See Also:
        isTypeOf(String)

      • isTypeOf

        Pipe<Vertex,Boolean> isTypeOf(String type)
        Returns a Pipe that computes for each input element whether it is an instance of type.

        Note: the created Pipe only checks if its input elements are strict instances of type. To check if they are instances of type or any of its subclasses see isKindOf(Vertex, String) and isKindOf(String).

        Parameters:
        type - the type to check
        Returns:
        a Pipe that computes for each input element whether it is an instance of type or any of its subclasses
        See Also:
        isTypeOf(Vertex, String)
